REFERENCE_DATE_TIME.comment: Reference date for julian days origin. The recommended reference date time is "19500101000000": January 1st 1950 00:00:00

DATE.comment: This is the original data describing the date, it must not be lost

DATE_EXT.long_name: DATE OF EACH EXTERNAL DATA MEASUREMENT
DATE_EXT.comment: This is the original data describing the date, it must not be lost

DAYD.long_name: DECIMAL JULIAN DAY (UTC) OF EACH MEASUREMENT
DAYD.conventions: Relative julian days with decimal part (as parts of the day)
DAYD.comment: Julian day of the measurement since REFERENCE_DATE_TIME. The integer part represents the day, the decimal part represents the time of the measurement. Date and time are in universal time coordinate.

DAYD_EXT.long_name: DECIMAL JULIAN DAY (UTC) OF EXTERNAL DATA MEASUREMENT
DAYD_EXT.conventions: Relative julian days with decimal part (as parts of the day)
DAYD_EXT.comment: Julian day of the measurement since REFERENCE_DATE_TIME. The integer part represents the day, the decimal part represents the time of the measurement. Date and time are in universal time coordinate.

LATX_EXT.long_name: LATITUDE OF EACH EXTERNAL DATA MEASUREMENT

LONX_EXT.long_name: LONGITUDE OF EACH EXTERNAL DATA MEASUREMENT

POSITION_QC.comment: Quality flag applied on the position of the measurement.

SPDC.comment: Ship speed from GPS (SOG - Speed Over Ground). If SOG not available, derived from last position

PRES.comment: Pressure inside TSG, this is an indication that pump is working properly

FLOW.long_name: MEASURING FLOW IN THE TSG INLET
FLOW.comment: Water pump discharge measurement in the TSG inlet, this is an indication that pump is working properly

CNDC.comment: Conductivity measured by TSG. This data may have been reduced with a median (recommended) or a mean

CNDC_STD.comment: Standard deviation of conductivity measured by TSG for data which have been reduced (with a mean or median)

CNDC_FREQ.comment: Sensor conductivity frequency measured by TSG

CNDC_CALCOEF.comment: Calibration coefficients are real value, date is in julian day from REFERENCE_DATE_TIME

CNDC_CALCOEF_CONV.comment: Calibration coefficient convention is an enumeration of coefficients name, ex: 'date','a','b','c','d','m','cpcor' or 'date','g','h','i','j','cpcor','ctcor'

CNDC_LINCOEF.comment: Calibration coefficients are real value, date is in julian day from REFERENCE_DATE_TIME

CNDC_LINCOEF_CONV.long_name: CONDUCTIVITY LINEAR DRIFT CORRECTION COEFFICIENTS CONVENTION
CNDC_LINCOEF_CONV.comment: Calibration coefficient convention is an enumeration of coefficients name, ex: 'slope','offset'

SSJT.comment: Temperature within TSG or water jacket temperature. Warning, this is not ocean SST temperature. It is used for salinity computation. The reduction applied is the same as for conductivity. Temperature is ITS-90

SSJT_QC.comment: Quality flag applied on water jacket temperature values

SSJT_STD.comment: Water jacket temperature standard deviation for data wich have been reduced (with a mean or median)

SSJT_CAL.comment: Water jacket temperature calibrated using linearization coefficients

SSJT_FREQ.comment: Frequency of water jacket temperature sensor

SSJT_CALCOEF.comment: Calibration coefficients are real value, date is in julian day from REFERENCE_DATE_TIME

SSJT_CALCOEF_CONV.comment: Calibration coefficient convention is an enumeration of coefficients name, ex: 'date','a','b','c','d','f0' or 'date','g','h','i','j','f0'

SSJT_LINCOEF.comment: Calibration coefficients are real value, date is in julian day from REFERENCE_DATE_TIME

SSJT_LINCOEF_CONV.long_name: TEMPERATURE LINEAR DRIFT CORRECTION COEFFICIENTS CONVENTION
SSJT_LINCOEF_CONV.comment: Calibration coefficient convention is an enumeration of coefficients name, ex: 'slope','offset'

SSJT_ADJUSTED.comment: Adjusted water jacket temperature with external data (ARGO,CTD,XBT,...)

SSJT_ADJUSTED_ERROR.long_name: ERROR ON ADJUSTED WATER JACKET TEMPERATURE
SSJT_ADJUSTED_ERROR.comment: Error on adjusted water jacket temperature with external data

SSJT_ADJUSTED_QC.comment: Quality flag applied on adjusted water jacket temperature values

SSJT_ADJUSTED_HIST.long_name: WATER JACKET TEMPERATURE ADJUSTED PROCESSING HISTORY
SSJT_ADJUSTED_HIST.comment: Water jacket temperature inside TSG adjusted processing history

SSPS.comment: Sea Surface Salinity (SSS) deduced from conductivity and water jacket temperature. This is the Ocean surface salinity. units = PSS.78 (Practical Salinity Scale)

SSPS_QC.comment: Quality flag applied on sea surface salinity values

SSPS_STD.comment: Standard deviation of sea surface salinity measured by TSG in case when CNDC_STD not available

SSPS_CAL.comment: Sea surface salinity calibrated deduced from conductivity and water jacket temperature

SSPS_ADJUSTED.comment: Sea surface salinity adjusted with external data (ARGO,CTD,XBT,...)

SSPS_ADJUSTED_ERROR.long_name: ERROR ON SEA SURFACE SALINITY ADJUSTED
SSPS_ADJUSTED_ERROR.comment: Error on sea surface salinity adjusted with external data

SSPS_ADJUSTED_QC.long_name: SEA SURFACE SALINITY ADJUSTED QUALITY FLAG
SSPS_ADJUSTED_QC.comment: Quality flag applied on adjusted  sea surface salinity

SSPS_ADJUSTED_HIST.long_name: SEA SURFACE SALINITY ADJUSTED PROCESSING HISTORY
SSPS_ADJUSTED_HIST.comment: Sea surface salinity adjusted processing history

SSPS_DEPH.long_name: NOMINAL DEPTH OF WATER INTAKE FOR SALINITY MEASUREMENT

SSPS_DEPH_MIN.long_name: MINIMUM DEPTH OF WATER INTAKE FOR SALINITY MEASUREMENT

SSPS_DEPH_MAX.long_name: MAXIMUM DEPTH OF WATER INTAKE FOR SALINITY MEASUREMENT

SSTP.comment: Sea Surface Temperature (SST) measured at intake with external instrument (TINT_TYPE, TINT_NUMBER). This is ocean surface temperature

SSTP_QC.comment: Quality flag applied on sea surface temperature values

SSTP_FREQ.comment: Frequency of external temperature sensor, used for SST measurement

SSTP_ADJUSTED_ERROR.long_name: ERROR ON SEA SURFACE TEMPERATURE ADJUSTED
SSTP_ADJUSTED_ERROR.comment: Error on sea surface temperature adjusted

SSTP_ADJUSTED_QC.long_name: SEA SURFACE TEMPERATURE ADJUSTED QUALITY FLAG
SSTP_ADJUSTED_QC.comment: Quality flag applied on sea surface temperature adjusted

SSTP_ADJUSTED_HIST.long_name: SEA SURFACE TEMPERATURE ADJUSTED PROCESSING HISTORY
SSTP_ADJUSTED_HIST.comment: Sea surface temperature adjusted processing history

SSTP_DEPH.long_name: NOMINAL DEPTH OF WATER INTAKE FOR TEMPERATURE MEASUREMENT

SSTP_DEPH_MIN.long_name: MINIMUM DEPTH OF WATER INTAKE FOR TEMPERATURE MEASUREMENT

SSTP_DEPH_MAX.long_name: MAXIMUM DEPTH OF WATER INTAKE FOR TEMPERATURE MEASUREMENT

SSTP_CALCOEF.comment: Calibration coefficients are real value, date is in julian day from REFERENCE_DATE_TIME

SSTP_CALCOEF_CONV.comment: Calibration coefficient convention is an enumeration of coefficients name, ex: 'date','a','b','c','d','f0' or 'date','g','h','i','j','f0'

SSTP_LINCOEF.comment: Calibration coefficients are real value, date is in julian day from REFERENCE_DATE_TIME

SSTP_LINCOEF_CONV.long_name: TEMPERATURE LINEAR DRIFT CORRECTION COEFFICIENTS CONVENTION
SSTP_LINCOEF_CONV.comment: Calibration coefficient convention is an enumeration of coefficients name, ex: 'slope','offset'

SSTP_EXT.long_name: SEA SURFACE TEMPERATURE FROM EXTERNAL DATA
SSTP_EXT.comment: Sea Surface Temperature (SST) from external data instrument (ARGO,CTD, XBT)

SSTP_EXT_QC.long_name: SEA SURFACE TEMPERATURE FROM EXTERNAL DATA QUALITY FLAG
SSTP_EXT_QC.comment: Quality flag applied on external sea surface temperature data values

SSTP_EXT_TYPE.long_name: TYPE OF EXTERNAL SEA SURFACE TEMPERATURE  DATA ORIGIN

SSPS_EXT.long_name: SEA SURFACE SALINITY FROM EXTERNAL DATA
SSPS_EXT.comment: Sea Surface Salinity (SSS) from external data instrument (WS,ARGO,CTD, XBT)

SSPS_EXT_QC.long_name: SEA SURFACE SALINITY FROM EXTERNAL DATA QUALITY FLAG
SSPS_EXT_QC.comment: Quality flag applied on external sea surface salinity data values

SSPS_EXT_TYPE.long_name: TYPE OF EXTERNAL SEA SURFACE SALINITY DATA ORIGIN

SSPS_EXT_ANALDATE.long_name: DATE OF WATER SAMPLE SURFACE SALINITY ANALYSIS
SSPS_EXT_ANALDATE.comment: Date of sea surface salinity water sample analysis

SSPS_EXT_BOTTLE.comment: The ID numbers of the sea surface salinity sampling bottles

CYCLE_MESURE.name: cycle_mesure
CYCLE_MESURE.comment: Cruise name or travel name. Example : EGEE6 or PAST0601

PROJECT_NAME.name: project_name
PROJECT_NAME.comment: Name of project which operates the TSG line. Example: SO-SSS

DATE_TSG.name: date_tsg
DATE_TSG.comment: Date of TSG installation, format : yyyymmddDDHHMMSS

TYPE_TSG.name: type_tsg
TYPE_TSG.comment: Thermosalinograph model number. Example : SBE21 or SBE45

DATE_TINT.name: date_tint
DATE_TINT.comment: Date of TINT installation, format: yyyymmddHHMMSS

TYPE_TINT.name: type_tint
TYPE_TINT.comment: Temperature sensor at intake. Example: SBE38

NUMBER_TINT.name: number_tint
NUMBER_TINT.comment: Intake temperature sensor serial number. Example: 3940

DATA_TYPE.name: data_type
DATA_TYPE.comment: Describe data type contained in file. Example: TRAJECTORY, PROFILE or TIME-SERIES

DATA_MODE.name: data_mode
DATA_MODE.comment: Indicate if the file contains real time or delayed mode data. R : real time data, D : delayed mode data

DATE_START.name: date_start
DATE_START.comment: Date of first measurements (UTC), format: yyyymmddHHMMSS

DATE_END.name: date_end
DATE_END.comment: Date of last measurements (UTC), format: yyyymmddHHMMSS

CONVENTIONS.name: Conventions
CONVENTIONS.comment: GOSUD NetCDF file format conventions, example: CF1.4, GOSUD 3.0

DATE_CREATION.name: date_creation
DATE_CREATION.comment: Date and time (UTC) of creation of this file, format: yyyymmddHHMMSS

DATE_UPDATE.name: date_update
DATE_UPDATE.comment: Date and time (UTC) of update of this file, format: yyyymmddHHMMSS

DATA_RESTRICTIONS.name: data_restrictions
DATA_RESTRICTIONS.comment: Restriction on use for these data, example: NONE

CITATION.name: citation
CITATION.comment: This citation should be used for publications. Example : "These data were collected and made freely available by the International GOSUD Project and the national programmes that contribute to it."

PI_NAME.name: pi_name
PI_NAME.string: Denis Diverres|David Varillon|Thierry Delcroix|Yves Gouriou|Bernard Bourles|Gilles Reverdin|Rosemary Morrow|Magali Krieger|Julien Perrier|Stephane Jacquin|Fabienne Gaillard
PI_NAME.comment: Name of the principal investigator in charge of the TSG line.

DATA_ACQUISITION.name: data_acquisition
DATA_ACQUISITION.comment: Acquisition data centre, example: SHOM, IRD, GENAVIR, CNRS,

PROCESSING_CENTRE.name: processing_centre
PROCESSING_CENTRE.comment: Processing data centre, example: SO-SSS, CORIOLIS, TSG_RECHERCHE, ...

PROCESSING_STATES.name: processing_states
PROCESSING_STATES.comment: 0A: RAW DATA|1A: CLIMATOLOGY CONTROL|1B: APPLICATION  OF QUALITY CODE AFTER VISUAL INSPECTION|1C: VALIDED BY PI|2C+: CALIBRATED DATA VALIDATED BY PI

WS_TYPE.name: ws_type
WS_TYPE.comment: Model of water sample. Default: NA, Not Available, Example: OSIL

TYPE_POSITION.name: type_position
TYPE_POSITION.comment: Description of navigation system. Example: GPS, GPS DIFFERENTIAL, ARGOS, INTERPOLATE, MANUAL, NONE, UNKNOW

HISTORY.name: history
HISTORY.comment: Provides an audit trail for modifications to the original data
